Sir Mix-a-Lot wrote the lyric “itty bitty waist and a round thing in your face” about other mother. Don’t fact check me.

Thank you Harpoon Productions for the early screening of this! There were a few elements to this thriller that I wish got further developed. We got flashbacks to the friendship and mentorship between Antonio Banderas and Alice Eve that were so minimal and randomly tossed into the story that they felt so misplaced. This movie was called ‘Cult Killer’ yet I felt like the last 20 minutes is really when it scratched the surface on the gruesome past of this…
Watching this after seeing Wicked is so wild. Justice for the wicked witch!! She’s just mad this little farm girl came in and stole her dead sisters shoes !!!

I really wanted to love Dan Levy’s feature film directorial debut because we know the guys got writing chops, but this just didn’t hit for me. It was really hard to connect to his character as we skipped a whole year of his grief and the grief we watched was a jaunt off to his pied-à-terre in Paris with his friends.

I hesitate to even call this a “disaster movie” because I hate to put it with the likes of lackluster movies in that genre. Bayona does something so different with this and somehow frightens us to our core and also moves us to tears with the perseverance and faith and friendship that these survivors have. Nothing about this felt cliche like the others in the genre. With this being based on a true story it also didn’t feel exploitative of…
